OL,3,CMatthew O'Toole breached MLA code of
OL,4,Cconduct by disclosing Lyons complaint
OL,6,FBut, in her report, Ms McCullough
OL,7,Fsaid: "It is my view that Mr O'Toole
OL,8,Fknew, or ought reasonably to have
OL,9,Fknown, that issuing a public press
OL,10,Frelease concerning an active and
OL,11,Fconfidential complaint submitted to
OL,12,Fthis Office was inappropriate and in
OL,13,Fbreach of Rule 12 of the MLA Code of
OL,14,FConduct."
OL,16,FShe added: "Confidentiality is of
OL,17,Fparamount importance to the work of
OL,18,Fthe Office of the Commissioner for
OL,19,FStandards.
