OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1771012680
OL,3,CMatthew O'Toole breached MLA code of
OL,4,Cconduct by disclosing Lyons complaint
OL,6,F"In my view, it is essential that
OL,7,Fbreaches of confidentiality are
OL,8,Ftreated with the seriousness they
OL,9,Fdeserve in order to safeguard the
OL,10,Fintegrity of the complaints process
OL,11,Fand to prevent the risk of misuse or
OL,12,Fharm that may arise from such
OL,13,Fbreaches."
OL,15,FMr O'Toole said: "The current MLA code
OL,16,Fand the interpretation applied means
OL,17,Fthat an MLA disclosing even the fact
OL,18,Fof a complaint is also technically a
OL,19,Fbreach of the code.
