OL,3,CMatthew O'Toole breached MLA code of
OL,4,Cconduct by disclosing Lyons complaint
OL,6,FHe added: "I am however pleased the
OL,7,Fprevious commissioner herself ` who
OL,8,Fconducted her enquiries in good faith
OL,9,F` agrees that this case raises
OL,10,F'important and legitimate questions'
OL,11,Fabout the drafting of the rules.
OL,13,F"For example, an MLA who confirmed
OL,14,Fpublicly they had referred themselves
OL,15,Fto the Commissioner would fall foul of
OL,16,Fthis rule too, demonstrating its
OL,17,Fperverse consequences.
OL,19,F"This rule is bizarre, and clearly
OL,20,Fneeds to be revisited."
